This species has been found in Ecuador and Colombia at very variable elevations from 1100-2700 m (Fig. 
92
).

The tip of the left antenna from the type specimen was broken during examination (Fig. 
16
). The paratype female is intact; however, the left orbicular spot is incomplete (Fig. 
22
). Otherwise, the female forewing is more brightly colored than that of the male basally where the antemedial and basal lines are almost inconspicuous. The female paratype from FSU has a different DNA voucher label from the voucher published at http://barcodinglife.com.
